The map is really tough to read because the street names are just placed randomly. The city plan is such that all the streets, especially in the Vedado neighborhood are arranged in an alpha numeric grid. This map does not adequately show that. We would need to have the street names all lined up such as this map shows (http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-r2XUDMm5wjQ/UEiEc_h8kGI/AAAAAAAAic8/PiLNAwe6WUg/s1600/mapa-havana-cuba.JPG) There you can see how the city is organized. I don't know how to change the location of a street name tag... If somebody tells me, I will do this myself. Thanks
closing_comment: Since all the streets are not the same distance, their names would never match as your example. OpenStreetMap recommends to not map for the renderer. http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Good_practice#Don.27t_map_for_the_renderer  Additionally, the renderer (Mapnik) automatically renders the name of the street based on the zoom level. If your example was possible, users zooming near the sea would not see the street name.  You can visit http://learnosm.org/ to learn more about mapping.
